\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 # AuralScript\par
\par
**AuralScript** converts audio files into structured text schemas that can be read and analyzed by a Large Language Model (LLM) like Claude.\par
\par
The core idea: AI music generators like Suno AI produce outputs that often drift from the intended style prompt. AuralScript closes the feedback loop \f1\emdash  extract acoustic features from the output, feed them to an LLM, and get data-driven suggestions on why the output drifted and what prompt adjustments to make.\par
\par
---\par
\par
## What it does\par
\par
AuralScript extracts and serializes the following from any MP3 or WAV file:\par
\par
| Section | What it captures |\par
|---|---|\par
| META | BPM, key, tempo stability, beat strength |\par
| ENERGY | RMS, dynamic range, loudness level |\par
| BASS | Sub vs mid-bass balance, guitar vs synth bass character |\par
| ONSET DENSITY | Arrangement busyness, hits per second |\par
| SPECTRUM | Brightness, spectral centroid, bandwidth |\par
| DISTORTION | High-frequency noise floor distortion estimate |\par
| STRUCTURE | Quiet/loud alternating pattern, verse-chorus detection |\par
| HARMONIC | Chord complexity, tonal stability, change rate |\par
| REVERB / ROOM | Decay time estimate, electronic vs organic instrument hint |\par
| STEREO WIDTH | Mono vs wide mix (M/S ratio) |\par
| TEXTURE | Harmonic/percussive balance, roughness, MFCCs |\par
| VOCAL | Vocal presence and character in mix |\par
| TRANSIENTS | Attack sharpness (Peak/Mean ratio) |\par
| WAVEFORM | ASCII amplitude plot of the full song |\par
| TIMELINE | 16-segment breakdown: energy, key, vocal, pitch confidence |\par
| PANNS TAGS | Neural audio tagging \emdash  genre, instrument, vocal style (optional) |\par
\par
---\par
\par
