## Installation\par
\par
### Step 1 \f1\emdash  Install Python 3.12\par
\par
Download from {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://www.python.org/downloads/ }}{\fldrslt{https://www.python.org/downloads/\ul0\cf0}}}}\f1\fs22\par
\par
**Critical:** On the first installer screen, check **"Add Python to PATH"**\par
\par
Verify:\par
```\par
python --version\par
```\par
\par
### Step 2 \emdash  Install core dependencies\par
\par
```\par
pip install librosa\par
pip install numpy\par
pip install scipy\par
pip install soundfile\par
```\par
\par
### Step 3 \emdash  Install PANNs (optional but recommended)\par
\par
PANNs adds neural audio tagging \emdash  genre, instrument, and vocal style classification using a model trained on 527 AudioSet sound categories.\par
\par
```\par
pip install torch --index-url {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu }}{\fldrslt{https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu\ul0\cf0}}}}\f1\fs22\par
pip install panns-inference\par
```\par
\par
Then manually download two files into `C:\\Users\\<yourname>\\panns_data\\`:\par
\par
**File 1 \emdash  Class labels CSV:**\par
```\par
{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://storage.googleapis.com/us_audioset/youtube_corpus/v1/csv/class_labels_indices.csv }}{\fldrslt{http://storage.googleapis.com/us_audioset/youtube_corpus/v1/csv/class_labels_indices.csv\ul0\cf0}}}}\f1\fs22\par
```\par
Save as: `class_labels_indices.csv`\par
\par
**File 2 \emdash  Model checkpoint (~500MB):**\par
```\par
{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://zenodo.org/record/3987831/files/Cnn14_mAP%3D0.431.pth?download=1 }}{\fldrslt{https://zenodo.org/record/3987831/files/Cnn14_mAP%3D0.431.pth?download=1\ul0\cf0}}}}\f1\fs22\par
```\par
Save as: `Cnn14_mAP=0.431.pth`\par
\par
> Note: PANNs has Windows-specific setup issues. If it doesn't work, AuralScript runs fine without it \emdash  all other sections still work.\par
\par
---\par
\par
## Usage\par
\par
### Basic run\par
```\par
python auralscript_extract.py "your_song.mp3"\par
```\par
Output saved as: `your_song_auralscript.txt`\par
\par
### Specify output path\par
```\par
python auralscript_extract.py "your_song.mp3" --out "results/song_v1.txt"\par
```\par
\par
### DAW-processed files\par
If the file has been through a DAW (edited, mixed, mastered beyond the raw Suno output), add `--processed`. This adjusts thresholds for the structure detector and distortion estimator:\par
```\par
python auralscript_extract.py "your_song.mp3" --processed\par
```\par
\par
---\par
\par
## The Suno AI workflow\par
\par
1. Write a style prompt in Suno AI and generate a song\par
2. Download the MP3\par
3. Run AuralScript on it\par
4. Fill in the SUNO TAGS section at the bottom of the output\par
5. Paste the full output to Claude (or another LLM)\par
6. Ask: *"Based on this AuralScript output and my style prompt, why did it drift and what should I change?"*\par
7. Iterate\par
\par
### Example prompt to Claude:\par
```\par
Here is my AuralScript output and my Suno style prompt.\par
The song was supposed to be 90s grunge with quiet verses and loud choruses.\par
Based on the data, what went wrong and what tags should I adjust?\par
\par
[paste AuralScript output]\par
\par
Style prompt used: [paste your Suno style prompt]\par
```\par
\par
---\par
\par
## What the data tells an LLM\par
\par
The key genre-separating signals discovered during development:\par
\par
| Signal | Electronic | Organic/Rock |\par
|---|---|---|\par
| Decay Consistency | ~0.000 | 0.3\endash 0.9 |\par
| Spectral Centroid | >4000 Hz | 2500\endash 3500 Hz |\par
| PANNs tags | Electronic, Synth, EDM | Guitar, Rock, Grunge |\par
| Tempo Stability | \f0\'b10.0 BPM | \'b10.5\f1\endash 2.0 BPM |\par
| Distortion HF/Mid | -6 to -8 dB | -10 to -14 dB |\par
\par
---\par
\par
## Limitations\par
\par
- **ZCR roughness** is unreliable for distinguishing distorted guitar from clean synth on compressed audio\par
- **Pitch confidence (PConf)** is low across all segments for dense/compressed mixes \emdash  this is expected, not a bug\par
- **Dynamic range** can read as 0 or absurdly high if the file has near-silence at start/end \emdash  v2.1 excludes bottom 5% RMS frames to mitigate this\par
- **PANNs** does not support Windows natively \emdash  requires manual file download workaround\par
- BPM sometimes halves or doubles \emdash  if the reading seems wrong, mentally multiply or divide by 2\par
\par
---\par
\par
## Background\par
\par
AuralScript was developed in a single session as an experiment in whether acoustic feature extraction could close the feedback loop on AI-generated music. The concept \emdash  extract features from AI music output, serialize to LLM-readable text, feed back to the AI ecosystem that generated it \emdash  appears to be novel. No prior art found for this specific closed-loop application.\par
\par
